.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple UNIX shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is a simple shell implementation that allows users to run commands in a UNIX-like environment. It is designed to be lightweight and easy to use, providing basic shell functionalities.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.
.SH USAGE
To run the shell, use the following command:
.B ./hsh
.PP
Once in the shell, you can enter commands directly. For example:
.RS
.B /bin/ls
.RE
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
In interactive mode, the shell will display a prompt (`($)`) and wait for user input. Users can type commands and press Enter to execute them.
.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
The shell can also be run in non-interactive mode by piping commands to it. For example:
.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.SH LIMITATIONS
This shell does not support advanced features such as:
.TP
.B - Arguments for commands
.B - Pipes and redirections
.B - Special characters (", ', &, #)
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns an exit status of 0 for successful commands and 1 for errors.
